olive oil
1 capsicum
1 bunch spring onion
½ tin sweetcorn
1 avocado
½ lemon
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag coriander
1 bag mint
1 packet sour cream
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 packet Smoked Cheddar Cheese
2 flatbreads
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend

• Chop capsicum. Thinly slice spring onion. Drain sweetcorn (1/2 tin for 2P/1 tin for 4P)
• Cut avocado in half, scoop out flesh and roughly chop. Slice lemon
• Toast or grill flat breads to your liking.

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat
• Season pork
• Cook pork and spice blend until cooked through 3-4 mins each side. Transfer to a plate
• Return pan to high heat. Cook capsicum and corn until tender, 3-4 mins. Remove from heat.

• In a bowl, add capsicum, corn, avo, spring onion, spinach, lemon juice and oil. Season and toss
• To the bowl, add torn coriander and mint. Toss
• Slice pork
• Plate up salad and pork
• Serve with sour cream, chipotle, Cheddar and flat breads.